msContents.summary: Scripture by various authors known as New Testament [p]

objectDesc.p: Parchment, 2.6x12.8 (34x27), 1 extant leaf(s), 2 column(s), 4 (?) line(s) per column, 20-28 characters per line, written in Greek/Latin.

handDesc.handNote: 300-399 Original scribe with professional hand (2 verses).

additions.p: The recto contains Eph. 6:5-6 written in Latin.

history.provenance: Excavated 1937-1938 by Evaristo Breccia at Sheikh-'Ibada, Miṣr.
Transferred to PSI XIII 1306, Biblioteca Medicea Laurentiana (Medicean Laurentian Library) at Firenze, Italia.
Transferred 1953 Dec 17 to Al-Matḥaf Al-Maṣri (Egyptian Museum) at Al Qāhirah, Miṣr.

msIdentifier.msName: SR 3796 25/1/55/2 (21), Al-Matḥaf Al-Maṣri (Egyptian Museum), Al Qāhirah, Miṣr.
